## 👋 About Me

I'm Oussama, a final-year engineering student specializing in **Network Security & Quality of Service** at POLYTECH Dijon, complementing my technical background with a **Master's in Business Administration** at IAE Dijon. I'm passionate about the ever-evolving landscape of cybersecurity — from hunting vulnerabilities in web applications to designing resilient network architectures that can withstand real-world threats.

What drives me is the intersection of **deep technical expertise and strategic thinking**. I don't just want to configure firewalls and write audit reports — I want to understand *why* systems fail, *how* attackers think, and *what* it truly takes to build infrastructure that organizations can trust.

I had the incredible opportunity to work as a Network Engineer Intern at **King Mongkut's University of Technology North Bangkok** in Thailand, where I collaborated with an international research team to optimize QoS for a robotic communication system. That experience reinforced my belief that great security and networking work is both a science and a craft.

